@namespace DotNetCloud.Modules.Email.UI

@*
    Help content for the Email module.
*@

<div class="help-content">
    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Overview</h2>
        <p>DotNetCloud Email provides a web-based email client with folder management, search, attachments, and signature settings. Compose, read, and organize your messages.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Composing Messages</h2>
        <p>Click <strong>Compose</strong> to open the message editor. Fill in the recipient(s), subject, and message body. The editor supports rich text formatting.</p>
        <p><strong>Attachments:</strong> Click the attachment icon or drag files onto the compose area to attach them.</p>
        <p><strong>Saving drafts:</strong> Unsent messages are automatically saved as drafts.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Folders</h2>
        <p>Standard folders include <strong>Inbox</strong>, <strong>Sent</strong>, <strong>Drafts</strong>, <strong>Spam</strong>, and <strong>Trash</strong>. Create custom folders for additional organization.</p>
        <p>Messages can be moved between folders by dragging or using the folder menu.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Search</h2>
        <p>Use the search bar to find messages by sender, subject, or content. Search across all folders including trash.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Signature Settings</h2>
        <p>Configure one or more email signatures in settings. Signatures can include rich text, images, and your contact information. Choose a default signature for new messages.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="help-section">
        <h2 class="help-section-title">Tips &amp; Tricks</h2>
        <ul class="help-tips">
            <li>Create filters to automatically sort incoming messages into folders.</li>
            <li>Use multiple signatures for different contexts (work, personal).</li>
            <li>Search operators can help narrow results: <code>from:</code>, <code>subject:</code>, <code>has:attachment</code>.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
</div>
